    "claim": "Per-program `subsidyFlowRate` is stored as a configured/requested value, but stop/cancel subtract this value from the current global subsidy flow (which can be lower in practice), and negative results are clamped to zero, so stopping one program can unintentionally terminate subsidy flow required by other still-running programs.",
    "impact": "Active programs can lose subsidy rewards prematurely, causing protocol-wide reward interruption and economic loss for stakers/LPs; this is especially dangerous with multiple concurrent programs sharing one global subsidy stream.",
    "paths": [
      "Start multiple subsidized programs so stored per-program subsidy deltas exceed current effective global subsidy flow.",
      "Call `stopFunding(programId)` or `cancelProgram(programId)` for one such program.",
      "`_updateSubsidyFlowRate` computes a negative new rate and forces the stream to `0`, halting subsidy distribution for remaining active programs."
    ]
  },
